It seems like the `XmlSerializer` constructor does cache a serialization for every type but `XmlSerializer.FromTypes()` does not . So potential fix could be pretty straightforward:
```C#
        public static XmlSerializer[] FromTypes(Type[] types)
        {
            if (types == null) throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(types));

            var serializers = new XmlSerializer[types.Length];
            for (int i = 0; i < types.Length; i++)
            {
                serializers[i] = new XmlSerializer(types[i]);
            }

            return serializers;
        }
```

